ThinkFeel: I think the artist felt many emotions - some difficult and some soothing. Like a memory can be troubling and meaningful, the imagery felt like it emerged from two places. I felt sorrow and hope. I felt like the artist experienced growth from making the mask. By working through the sadness, they learned that they can grow as a person.
Describe: The background of purple, white, and green appear to be the distant environment. The black growth that looks like trees or plants speak of time spent in that environment. The added markings of gold with black fine lines seem to suggest pleasures that occurred after the trauma. The black stars or bird shapes seem like they are added hints at hopeful experiences that come after healing.
Understanding: I gained a connect with another human that has experienced pain and trauma. I an tearing up as I type. The connects we make in making art are images in ourselves that need a place outside of ourselves. I am happy to have looked at this revealing event. I feel a shared emotion with the artist. I know it was hard to let the trauma emerge. It makes me also remember my trauma. But that is healthy too because I have hopeful experiences in my future as well. I am thankful the artist felt human and shared this human expression with other, as well as with themself.

ThinkFeel: This object seems to contain a lot of information that I am unable to decipher. The delicacy and precision of the color choices suggests a connection to a specific cultural tradition it feels like there is an exact meaning to it. The purple part of the face suggests the Purple Heart decoration and the splotches of contrasting color suggest specific injuries, possibly. That the top of the head is the color of a robin's egg is very evocative of the sky, perhaps a memory of being transported while injured. The decoration of the eyebrows, eyes and lips with metallic paint or foil reminds me of an Egyptian sarcophagus and has a funereal aspect to it, like the artist is memorializing someone, perhaps their younger self..
Describe: An oval face mask painted two-thirds in purple and one-third in an eggshell blue with splotches of contrasting blue and purple hues. The division is asymmetric with the left eye entirely in the blue and the right eye half in the purple. The eyebrows, eyes and mouth are detailed with metallic gold.
Understanding: This object seems very mysterious to me, but it is also the product of very specific choices of color and symmetry. I don't know that I have any new knowledge as result of looking at it, but I think I have a direct understanding of some the artists' experience.

ThinkFeel: My heart rate speeds up. I feel horrified, sad, numb and just terrible. I wonder what happened to the artist who made this mask and what experiences they are trying to heal from.
Describe: The mask is white and the lips are sewn shut. The upper part of the mask is black, specifically the upper brain. There are nails or sharp objects glued to this part of the mask, and what look like painted eyes that are open. The eyes of the mask are rimmed in reddish pink.
Understanding: I think this object resonated with me because of its visual depiction of inner trauma. It helped me understand inner horror in a person. It showed the way in which a person could feel silenced, deeply wounded, horrified, saddened and violated all at the same time and not necessarily know how to express or find healing from these feelings and experiences.
